[00:00.16]If my name ever crosses your mind one day,
[00:05.91]If you hear my voice when you kneel and pray,
[00:12.49]Don’t lift me up, don’t sing my praise,
[00:19.03]I’m just a sinner saved by mercy and grace.
[00:24.79]I’ve seen this world turn bitter and mean,
[00:28.51]Hearts grow hard where love should be,
[00:31.14]And it cuts me deep, the pain I see,
[00:35.11]Lord knows this life can be heavy on me.
[00:38.72]Mm-hmm… mercy, Lord
[00:42.94]Yes, grace…
[00:44.98]If my life ever says a word at all—
[00:49.98]Let it tell ‘em ‘bout the Lord
[00:53.08]If my feet ever walks a narrow road—
[00:57.68]Point ‘em to the cross
[01:00.35]Don’t remember me—
[01:02.36]Remember the cross
[01:03.27]The blood that was shed—
[01:05.88]For the sinner lost
[01:07.39]If my voice moves your heart to believe—
[01:11.14]Fall on your knees
[01:12.86]At the foot of that old rugged tree
[01:16.48]I’m just a sign on a dusty road—
[01:21.29]Pointin’ home
[01:22.32]To a Savior who carried the load—
[01:25.68]Jesus bore it all
[01:27.35]If you see anything good in me—
[01:31.32]Give Him the glory
[01:33.19]Let it lead you straight to Jesus, not me
[01:37.34]I love every soul, the broken, the weak,
[01:43.20]The ones who still think they’re too far gone to reach,
[01:51.71]I’ve sat with the hurt, I’ve heard their cries,
[01:59.64]Seen hope come alive through tear-filled eyes.
[02:05.02]This world’s got a way of tearing you down,
[02:13.60]Chewing up faith, grinding saints in the ground,
[02:20.18]But there’s a hope that never runs dry—
[02:27.83]It stood in a grave… and walked out alive.
[02:34.81]He got up!
[02:37.09]Yes He did!
[02:39.79]I ain’t the truth, I ain’t the way—
[02:42.98]Jesus Is!
[02:43.78]I’m just a voice trying to say—
[02:45.95]He saves!
[02:46.62]Don’t remember me—
[02:48.54]Remember the cross
[02:49.81]The nails, the thorns—
[02:52.18]The sacri-fice
[02:53.16]If my song ever reaches your soul—
[02:56.96]Let Him take control
[02:58.70]Fall down at Calvary
[03:00.67]I’m just a witness, I can't save—
[03:05.60]Give it! to a risen King and an empty grave—
[03:11.68]The grave couldn’t hold Him!
[03:15.17]If you hear anything when I speak—
[03:18.96]Hear Jesus!
[03:20.35]Let it sound like Jesus calling you, not me
[03:24.93]I didn’t save you
[03:26.40]He Does!
[03:27.42]I didn’t bleed
[03:28.69]He Did!
[03:29.49]I didn’t rise on the third day
[03:32.08]Jesus did!
[03:33.02]I didn’t break those chains you wear
[03:35.38]He broke ‘em!
[03:36.42]I just know the One who meets you there
[03:38.86]Thank You, Lord!
[03:40.21]So don’t remember me—
[03:41.73]Remember His name!
[03:42.53]The One who took our guilt and shame—
[03:45.04]Jesus!
[03:45.84]If my life ever leaves a trace—
[03:47.52]Let it point to grace!
[03:49.10]And mercy flowing from that place
[03:50.85]When my days are done and my voice is still—
[04:00.97]He’s still God!
[04:05.11]Let the echo stand on that lonely hill—
[04:13.30]Calvary!
[04:14.97]Remember Jesus…
[04:16.63]Don’t remember me
[04:19.81]Remember the cross…
[04:22.61]Remember His name…
[04:25.81]Jesus… Jesus…